<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="53e89196-5feb-5eb0-af5f-a389d281290f" activityNameId="06ffc039-f73b-440c-a5a0-8dc7393a5e71" parentActivityId="fb2d2fa2-5985-5d41-9c12-db8f93422eff" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">concrete block production</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">From the reception of raw materials at the concrete block factory.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the concrete block produced at the factory gate. The dataset does not include infrastructure, administration and factory maintenance.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset describes the production of concrete blocks in the Global geography. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">This dataset was built as a weighted average of regional datasets of the same activityName. Uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">The dataset includes the reception of materials, dosing and mixing, block production by vibration, curing and storage.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="27f6acbc-2350-450e-9762-1ce00e12ecba">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2395:Manufacture of articles of concrete, cement and plaster</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="7846b897-7c04-4f9f-b607-2b83fcd9a74c">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoW</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset is a weighted average built from the following geographies: BR, EC.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Current production technology. The dataset covers the main technologies for concrete block production in Brazil and Ecuador. The manufacturing process begins by dosing and mixing the cement, aggregates and water to make concrete. In the block machine, the steel cast is filled with concrete and the block is shaped and compacted by vibration. The fresh concrete block is then transported to the curing chambers. The cure can be done in the following ways: 1) naturally, leaving the blocks in closed chambers with no water addition; 2) wet cure, spraying water over the blocks to keep relative humidity high in order to ensure proper hydration of the cement; 3) thermal cure with steam, which enables the cement to hydrate faster than in the wet cure and lowers concrete shrinkage. The blocks are then packed in pallets and stored. The process can happen with various automation levels and different types and sizes of block machines. It is common to produce various block shapes and compressive strength classes in a single factory, as well as concrete pavers.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2012-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset is considered valid from the earliest start date (2012) until the latest end date (2023) of the regional datasets (BR and EC) of the same activity name.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
